headline: Why Accenture Stock Slumped Today
summary: Accenture (NYSE: ACN) was in the news Tuesday for yet another of the acquisitive company's asset buys.  Accenture's share price eroded by more than 2% on a day when the S&P 500 index basically traded flat.  Before market open that morning, the frequently acquisitive Accenture announced that it has agreed to purchase privately held AOX.
